        "created_at": "2018-07-12T16:10:30.664Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the hints!</p>\n<p>Yes, indeed the problem was about the mixing of fork (my code) and thread creation (in foundationDB init).</p>\n<p>Cf. <a href=\"https://thorstenball.com/blog/2014/10/13/why-threads-cant-fork/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://thorstenball.com/blog/2014/10/13/why-threads-cant-fork/</a> for a brief discussion.</p>\n<p>The solution in my case was to init foundationDB late, i.e. in each fork()ed child.</p>",
